00:02:34.060 --> 00:02:35.990 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: So let's start
at the beginning

00:02:35.990 --> 00:02:38.320 align:middle line:90%
of this eclipse thing.

00:02:38.320 --> 00:02:40.740 align:middle line:90%
Who's Maurice Allais?

00:02:40.740 --> 00:02:44.740 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: Allais was the guy--
he was a French genius-- who

00:02:44.740 --> 00:02:46.535 align:middle line:84%
actually always wanted
to be a physicist.

00:02:46.535 --> 00:02:48.410 align:middle line:84%
And his mommy told him
he had to do something

00:02:48.410 --> 00:02:51.100 align:middle line:84%
that would be
economically reasonable.

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:53.245 align:middle line:84%
So he became an
economist, and in 1988, he

00:02:53.245 --> 00:02:56.040 align:middle line:90%
won a Nobel Prize for economics.

00:02:56.040 --> 00:02:59.180 align:middle line:84%
But he kept an
exquisite track record

00:02:59.180 --> 00:03:01.180 align:middle line:84%
with the French
Academy of Sciences,

00:03:01.180 --> 00:03:03.780 align:middle line:84%
published paper after
paper in physics,

00:03:03.780 --> 00:03:08.270 align:middle line:84%
and began experimenting in
the '50s with pendulums,

00:03:08.270 --> 00:03:11.030 align:middle line:84%
except not those long
Foucault pendulums

00:03:11.030 --> 00:03:15.420 align:middle line:84%
you see in museums with the very
long wire and the long swing

00:03:15.420 --> 00:03:16.190 align:middle line:90%
rate.

00:03:16.190 --> 00:03:19.390 align:middle line:84%
He invented something called
a periconical pendulum, which

00:03:19.390 --> 00:03:22.340 align:middle line:84%
is probably from the ceiling
here maybe to the top

00:03:22.340 --> 00:03:25.410 align:middle line:84%
your head, which has
a much faster period.

00:03:25.410 --> 00:03:29.320 align:middle line:84%
And he was able to,
using this pendulum,

00:03:29.320 --> 00:03:34.350 align:middle line:84%
chart all kinds of unseen
stresses and strains, what

00:03:34.350 --> 00:03:37.540 align:middle line:84%
he called the
anisotropy of space,

00:03:37.540 --> 00:03:39.410 align:middle line:84%
that there was some
kind of medium,

00:03:39.410 --> 00:03:42.310 align:middle line:90%
some kind of matrix-- the ether.

00:03:42.310 --> 00:03:45.170 align:middle line:84%
And in 1954, using
this gadget that you

00:03:45.170 --> 00:03:48.800 align:middle line:84%
can see on screen, which is an
actual shot in his laboratory,

00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:50.870 align:middle line:84%
which was underground
in a basement, sealed

00:03:50.870 --> 00:03:54.930 align:middle line:84%
off, no temperature variations,
no air currents and all that,

00:03:54.930 --> 00:03:56.850 align:middle line:84%
he would do
month-long experiments

00:03:56.850 --> 00:03:59.740 align:middle line:84%
with these pendulums, looking
at periods and alignments

00:03:59.740 --> 00:04:00.640 align:middle line:90%
and all that.

00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:05.660 align:middle line:84%
Well-- this is one of his
lab technicians-- in 1954,

00:04:05.660 --> 00:04:09.920 align:middle line:84%
there happened to be a partial
eclipse of the sun over Paris.

00:04:09.920 --> 00:04:10.805 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't total.

00:04:10.805 --> 00:04:12.340 align:middle line:90%
It was partial.

00:04:12.340 --> 00:04:14.200 align:middle line:84%
He was doing something
else, probably

00:04:14.200 --> 00:04:16.360 align:middle line:84%
sleeping, because they
had to do 24-hour shifts

00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:18.310 align:middle line:84%
to do this kind of
data collection.

00:04:18.310 --> 00:04:23.080 align:middle line:84%
His chief laboratory
scientist, the head of his lab,

00:04:23.080 --> 00:04:25.580 align:middle line:84%
was doing the experiments
with the pendulum

00:04:25.580 --> 00:04:30.790 align:middle line:84%
and found, during this
eclipse, a stunning phenomenon,

00:04:30.790 --> 00:04:33.110 align:middle line:84%
an anomalous phenomenon
with the pendulum

00:04:33.110 --> 00:04:38.160 align:middle line:84%
where, as the moon moved
across the sun, the pendulum,

00:04:38.160 --> 00:04:41.000 align:middle line:84%
instead of continuing to
progress in an azimuth,

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:45.060 align:middle line:84%
meaning it would walk its way
around a circle, it suddenly--

00:04:45.060 --> 00:04:48.220 align:middle line:84%
and this is a schematic
of his actual diagram

00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:51.460 align:middle line:84%
of the experiment-- it
began to go backwards.

00:04:51.460 --> 00:04:54.900 align:middle line:84%
It began to literally change
by 13 and 1/2 degrees,

00:04:54.900 --> 00:04:56.990 align:middle line:84%
I think, in the
period of an hour

00:04:56.990 --> 00:05:00.690 align:middle line:84%
as the eclipse approached the
maximum amount there in Paris.

00:05:00.690 --> 00:05:02.020 align:middle line:90%
And then it reversed its trend.

00:05:02.020 --> 00:05:04.460 align:middle line:84%
This is a graph showing
the trend curve, which

00:05:04.460 --> 00:05:06.860 align:middle line:84%
is the red line sloping
down to the right.

00:05:06.860 --> 00:05:09.020 align:middle line:84%
Then you can see the
three green lines.

00:05:09.020 --> 00:05:10.690 align:middle line:84%
That's the beginning,
the middle,

00:05:10.690 --> 00:05:12.790 align:middle line:84%
and the end of the eclipse,
as seen from Paris.

00:05:12.790 --> 00:05:16.190 align:middle line:84%
All the action was in the
first half of the eclipse,

00:05:16.190 --> 00:05:18.960 align:middle line:90%
up until the midpoint.

00:05:18.960 --> 00:05:21.330 align:middle line:84%
These are data that he
was able to collect,

00:05:21.330 --> 00:05:27.000 align:middle line:84%
superimposed on each other,
from a second eclipse in 1959.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:29.560 align:middle line:84%
And as you know, science
is nothing but replication.

00:05:29.560 --> 00:05:31.590 align:middle line:84%
If you see something
once, it could

00:05:31.590 --> 00:05:34.560 align:middle line:84%
be an anomaly, it could be just
a weird accident, coincidence,

00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:35.430 align:middle line:90%
whatever.

00:05:35.430 --> 00:05:38.070 align:middle line:84%
You see it more
than once-- well,

00:05:38.070 --> 00:05:42.620 align:middle line:84%
Allais saw the same bizarre
pendulum behavior twice

00:05:42.620 --> 00:05:45.550 align:middle line:84%
at an eclipse that
crossed over Paris.

00:05:45.550 --> 00:05:48.550 align:middle line:84%
Now this is called
the Allais effect.

00:05:48.550 --> 00:05:52.890 align:middle line:84%
And it leads us into this
extraordinary, almost sci-fi

00:05:52.890 --> 00:05:56.840 align:middle line:84%
world of a parallel science
that has been suppressed,

00:05:56.840 --> 00:06:01.090 align:middle line:84%
which we call hyperdimensional
physics, which is basically

00:06:01.090 --> 00:06:03.180 align:middle line:84%
the way the universe
really runs,

00:06:03.180 --> 00:06:06.880 align:middle line:84%
that, for the last several
years, the folks in charge

00:06:06.880 --> 00:06:09.620 align:middle line:84%
have apparently not
wanted us to know about.

00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:11.759 align:middle line:84%
And it's these
democratized experiments,

00:06:11.759 --> 00:06:14.050 align:middle line:84%
including what we're going
to be doing in this upcoming

00:06:14.050 --> 00:06:16.080 align:middle line:84%
eclipse, that we think
are going to finally blow

00:06:16.080 --> 00:06:18.990 align:middle line:84%
the doors off the way
things really work.

00:06:18.990 --> 00:06:21.510 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: So what is this
hyperdimensional torsion field

00:06:21.510 --> 00:06:22.810 align:middle line:90%
physics?

00:06:22.810 --> 00:06:24.680 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: Well,
our model, buttressed

00:06:24.680 --> 00:06:28.990 align:middle line:84%
by Allais's experimental
data, space is not empty.

00:06:28.990 --> 00:06:29.780 align:middle line:90%
There is a matrix.

00:06:29.780 --> 00:06:31.200 align:middle line:90%
There is an ether.

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:34.590 align:middle line:84%
And rotating objects
interact with each other

00:06:34.590 --> 00:06:38.290 align:middle line:84%
through, you could call it, the
Einstein space-time continuum.

00:06:38.290 --> 00:06:39.710 align:middle line:90%
It has a lot of different names.

00:06:39.710 --> 00:06:43.875 align:middle line:84%
It's basically the stuff
between atoms, between matter

00:06:43.875 --> 00:06:45.320 align:middle line:90%
as we know it.

00:06:45.320 --> 00:06:50.550 align:middle line:84%
And apparently, if matter is
organized so that it rotates,

00:06:50.550 --> 00:06:54.290 align:middle line:84%
it generates waves
in this matrix that

00:06:54.290 --> 00:06:58.460 align:middle line:84%
communicate to other
rotating bodies in excess

00:06:58.460 --> 00:06:59.460 align:middle line:90%
of the speed of light.

00:06:59.460 --> 00:07:02.010 align:middle line:84%
This goes back to
Einstein and Carton

00:07:02.010 --> 00:07:03.930 align:middle line:84%
and some equations
they put together back

00:07:03.930 --> 00:07:07.750 align:middle line:84%
in 1913 that turned out to
be partially right and mostly

00:07:07.750 --> 00:07:11.140 align:middle line:84%
wrong, because the Carton
version of relativity

00:07:11.140 --> 00:07:14.210 align:middle line:84%
for torsion fields was
that they were static,

00:07:14.210 --> 00:07:16.930 align:middle line:84%
they wouldn't move,
and they were so tiny

00:07:16.930 --> 00:07:20.550 align:middle line:84%
that they would be undetectable
at the normal, everyday

00:07:20.550 --> 00:07:22.440 align:middle line:90%
laboratory level.

00:07:22.440 --> 00:07:24.280 align:middle line:84%
Years later,
physicists discovered

00:07:24.280 --> 00:07:28.240 align:middle line:84%
that, in fact, these waves
are much more powerful,

00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:32.190 align:middle line:84%
something like 22
orders of magnitude.

00:07:32.190 --> 00:07:35.770 align:middle line:90%
That's 1 followed by 21 zeros.

00:07:35.770 --> 00:07:38.040 align:middle line:84%
So they can have
real-world effects.

00:07:38.040 --> 00:07:41.240 align:middle line:84%
And it looks like Allais was
the first modern physicist

00:07:41.240 --> 00:07:42.010 align:middle line:90%
to discover them.

00:07:42.010 --> 00:07:45.300 align:middle line:84%
Now, what we did separately,
not knowing of Allais's work,

00:07:45.300 --> 00:07:48.802 align:middle line:84%
we worked on the theory
of rotating planets.

00:07:48.802 --> 00:07:50.260 align:middle line:84%
And on the screen
there, you'll see

00:07:50.260 --> 00:07:54.090 align:middle line:84%
the mathematics from,
basically, the--

00:07:54.090 --> 00:07:55.240 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Jupiter.

00:07:55.240 --> 00:07:56.700 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND:
--Jupiter on the left

00:07:56.700 --> 00:08:00.300 align:middle line:84%
and the circumscribed double
tetrahedra on the right.

00:08:00.300 --> 00:08:02.480 align:middle line:84%
The physics, as we
have figured it out,

00:08:02.480 --> 00:08:06.110 align:middle line:84%
tends to show these
geometric alignments

00:08:06.110 --> 00:08:09.830 align:middle line:84%
on the surface of rotating
bodies, like planets and stars.

00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:13.190 align:middle line:84%
So you have solar events,
you have geophysical events,

00:08:13.190 --> 00:08:15.930 align:middle line:84%
you have volcanoes or the
Great Red Spot on Jupiter,

00:08:15.930 --> 00:08:18.910 align:middle line:84%
coming up in accordance
with this geometry, which

00:08:18.910 --> 00:08:22.300 align:middle line:84%
is a signature that,
at the unseen level,

00:08:22.300 --> 00:08:25.190 align:middle line:84%
at the realm of
the level of space,

00:08:25.190 --> 00:08:28.160 align:middle line:84%
these rotating objects are
communicating to other rotating

00:08:28.160 --> 00:08:30.150 align:middle line:84%
objects, and they're
talking to each other.

00:08:30.150 --> 00:08:31.350 align:middle line:90%
They're communicating.

00:08:31.350 --> 00:08:34.610 align:middle line:84%
And there are now
experiments, like Allais,

00:08:34.610 --> 00:08:37.340 align:middle line:84%
which we believe have
actually detected

00:08:37.340 --> 00:08:40.299 align:middle line:84%
these waves of
interfering action

00:08:40.299 --> 00:08:42.340 align:middle line:90%
between these separate bodies.

00:08:42.340 --> 00:08:44.880 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: So in the
eclipse, the moon

00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:47.170 align:middle line:84%
passing in front of
the sun is causing

00:08:47.170 --> 00:08:52.080 align:middle line:84%
like a glitch in the
waves that are moving.

00:08:52.080 --> 00:08:54.990 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: As George Lucas
said, a "tremor in the Force."

00:08:54.990 --> 00:08:56.680 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: A tremor in
the Force, indeed.

00:08:56.680 --> 00:08:59.240 align:middle line:84%
So how's the coming
solar eclipse

00:08:59.240 --> 00:09:02.440 align:middle line:84%
relate to the torsion
hyperdimensional physics?

00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:04.945 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: Well, for
one thing, it's unique.

00:09:04.945 --> 00:09:06.570 align:middle line:84%
It hasn't happened
in the United States

00:09:06.570 --> 00:09:08.780 align:middle line:84%
that we had an
eclipse for 18 years.

00:09:08.780 --> 00:09:11.280 align:middle line:84%
For another, it's not just
your ordinary eclipse.

00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:14.270 align:middle line:84%
A total eclipse is
when the moon is

00:09:14.270 --> 00:09:15.770 align:middle line:84%
at the right distance
from the Earth

00:09:15.770 --> 00:09:17.600 align:middle line:84%
so it completely
blots out the sun,

00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:19.490 align:middle line:84%
and you see the
much fainter corona

00:09:19.490 --> 00:09:23.260 align:middle line:84%
around the sun, super hot
plasma streaming off into space.

00:09:23.260 --> 00:09:26.050 align:middle line:84%
This is what's called
an annular eclipse,

00:09:26.050 --> 00:09:29.830 align:middle line:84%
meaning the moon is far
enough away from the Earth

00:09:29.830 --> 00:09:31.900 align:middle line:84%
that the shadow doesn't
reach the Earth.

00:09:31.900 --> 00:09:34.320 align:middle line:84%
So what you'll see in
this eclipse track,

00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:38.680 align:middle line:84%
if you were in China or in Tokyo
or in the American Southwest,

00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:41.560 align:middle line:84%
over the space of several
hours, as the Earth is rotating

00:09:41.560 --> 00:09:43.590 align:middle line:84%
and the moon is moving
around the Earth,

00:09:43.590 --> 00:09:46.510 align:middle line:84%
you will see this
shadow, or this

00:09:46.510 --> 00:09:50.480 align:middle line:84%
annulus, projected in
the sky against the sun.

00:09:50.480 --> 00:09:54.170 align:middle line:84%
So you'll see what's basically
called a ring of fire.

00:09:54.170 --> 00:09:56.670 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to be
incredibly interesting,

00:09:56.670 --> 00:09:59.150 align:middle line:84%
because the average
daylight will not

00:09:59.150 --> 00:10:00.920 align:middle line:90%
appear that much different.

00:10:00.920 --> 00:10:04.530 align:middle line:84%
The photosphere of the sun is so
bright compared to the corona.

00:10:04.530 --> 00:10:06.970 align:middle line:84%
It's about a million times
brighter than the corona.

00:10:06.970 --> 00:10:11.990 align:middle line:84%
So it'll appear to be
like a cloudy afternoon.

00:10:11.990 --> 00:10:16.800 align:middle line:84%
But birds and other
animals may respond

00:10:16.800 --> 00:10:22.790 align:middle line:84%
not to the light change, but
to the torsion field phenomenon

00:10:22.790 --> 00:10:26.200 align:middle line:84%
change as the Allais
effect takes place

00:10:26.200 --> 00:10:27.977 align:middle line:84%
in all kinds of
living organisms.

