00:25:25.050 --> 00:25:40.020 align:middle line:90%


00:25:40.020 --> 00:25:41.190 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Hey, I'm Jay Weidner.

00:25:41.190 --> 00:25:43.399 align:middle line:84%
We're back with
"Gaiam Inspirations"

00:25:43.399 --> 00:25:44.440 align:middle line:90%
with Richard C. Hoagland.

00:25:44.440 --> 00:25:47.150 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about the
eclipse, the Venus transit,

00:25:47.150 --> 00:25:49.560 align:middle line:84%
and the end of the
Mayan calendar.

00:25:49.560 --> 00:25:52.027 align:middle line:84%
So Richard, let's get back
to the physics and things.

00:25:52.027 --> 00:25:53.860 align:middle line:84%
We're going to talk
about another guy that's

00:25:53.860 --> 00:25:55.500 align:middle line:84%
been a big influence
on all this,

00:25:55.500 --> 00:25:57.940 align:middle line:84%
a Russian named
Nikolai-- I hope I

00:25:57.940 --> 00:25:59.537 align:middle line:90%
pronounce this right-- Kozyrev.

00:25:59.537 --> 00:26:00.370 align:middle line:90%
>>HOAGLAND: Perfect.

00:26:00.370 --> 00:26:01.078 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Thank you.

00:26:01.078 --> 00:26:02.550 align:middle line:90%
And so who is he?

00:26:02.550 --> 00:26:04.530 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: He's
another replicator.

00:26:04.530 --> 00:26:07.560 align:middle line:90%
Not like on "Stargate."

00:26:07.560 --> 00:26:12.000 align:middle line:84%
Science has to be performed
to where independent guys come

00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:14.730 align:middle line:84%
to the same conclusion based
on different experiments that

00:26:14.730 --> 00:26:16.250 align:middle line:90%
show the same stuff.

00:26:16.250 --> 00:26:21.660 align:middle line:84%
Kozyrev was thrown in the Gulag
by Stalin back in the 1930s.

00:26:21.660 --> 00:26:24.880 align:middle line:84%
Young guy, incredible
genius, promising career,

00:26:24.880 --> 00:26:28.165 align:middle line:84%
ripped out of his
academic-- because Stalin

00:26:28.165 --> 00:26:30.230 align:middle line:84%
was terrified of the
scientists, because they're

00:26:30.230 --> 00:26:31.702 align:middle line:90%
the ones that knew stuff.

00:26:31.702 --> 00:26:33.660 align:middle line:84%
So he basically murdered
a whole bunch of them,

00:26:33.660 --> 00:26:36.580 align:middle line:90%
and Kozyrev got swept up in it.

00:26:36.580 --> 00:26:39.950 align:middle line:84%
He was let out just
after World War II.

00:26:39.950 --> 00:26:44.040 align:middle line:84%
In those years in the Gulag,
when he had nothing to do,

00:26:44.040 --> 00:26:47.140 align:middle line:84%
when he was freezing to death,
when he was starving to death,

00:26:47.140 --> 00:26:49.130 align:middle line:90%
all he could do was think.

00:26:49.130 --> 00:26:50.700 align:middle line:90%
So he was an astrophysicist.

00:26:50.700 --> 00:26:54.230 align:middle line:84%
So he went back and,
from first causes,

00:26:54.230 --> 00:26:56.650 align:middle line:84%
recalculated
everything he thought

00:26:56.650 --> 00:26:58.630 align:middle line:84%
he'd known from
his academic trip

00:26:58.630 --> 00:27:03.580 align:middle line:84%
into basic questions
like why do stars shine?

00:27:03.580 --> 00:27:06.400 align:middle line:84%
And he said that
they cannot shine,

00:27:06.400 --> 00:27:09.560 align:middle line:84%
according to his conceptual
modeling-- remember,

00:27:09.560 --> 00:27:12.700 align:middle line:84%
in his cell, middle of
the night, long winters,

00:27:12.700 --> 00:27:15.220 align:middle line:84%
long bread lines,
long everything.

00:27:15.220 --> 00:27:18.020 align:middle line:84%
And basically, it was hard
labor with a death sentence

00:27:18.020 --> 00:27:19.170 align:middle line:90%
at the end.

00:27:19.170 --> 00:27:22.450 align:middle line:84%
He's thinking about these
cosmic ideas with the freedom

00:27:22.450 --> 00:27:24.910 align:middle line:90%
to do nothing but think.

00:27:24.910 --> 00:27:27.661 align:middle line:84%
Not exactly what I would
prefer to do to think.

00:27:27.661 --> 00:27:29.660 align:middle line:84%
But he came to the same
conclusion that we have,

00:27:29.660 --> 00:27:33.290 align:middle line:84%
which is physical laws,
as currently put forward

00:27:33.290 --> 00:27:35.930 align:middle line:84%
by science, cannot explain
the really interesting stuff

00:27:35.930 --> 00:27:37.080 align:middle line:90%
in the universe.

00:27:37.080 --> 00:27:38.000 align:middle line:90%
Well, he went further.

00:27:38.000 --> 00:27:40.230 align:middle line:84%
He devised
instrumentation to begin

00:27:40.230 --> 00:27:45.250 align:middle line:84%
to measure what he called the
physical properties of time.

00:27:45.250 --> 00:27:46.830 align:middle line:90%
And this is-- what is it?

00:27:46.830 --> 00:27:49.520 align:middle line:90%
It's a torsion pendulum.

00:27:49.520 --> 00:27:52.030 align:middle line:90%
It rotates.

00:27:52.030 --> 00:27:54.810 align:middle line:84%
So he's at the same level
of rotation and inertia

00:27:54.810 --> 00:27:57.320 align:middle line:84%
that Allais was
and De Palma was.

00:27:57.320 --> 00:28:00.390 align:middle line:84%
He found that, if you
vibrate matter, just

00:28:00.390 --> 00:28:03.320 align:middle line:84%
shake it like the little
tuning fork in the Accutron,

00:28:03.320 --> 00:28:07.710 align:middle line:84%
you can see from the graph,
it loses or gains weight.

00:28:07.710 --> 00:28:09.450 align:middle line:90%
Just shaking it.

00:28:09.450 --> 00:28:11.350 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't do
it continuously,

00:28:11.350 --> 00:28:12.610 align:middle line:90%
like a continuous curve.

00:28:12.610 --> 00:28:16.650 align:middle line:84%
It does it in quantum steps,
meaning that, at some level,

00:28:16.650 --> 00:28:19.800 align:middle line:84%
the ether is quantitized,
far below what's

00:28:19.800 --> 00:28:21.510 align:middle line:90%
called the Planck level.

00:28:21.510 --> 00:28:24.920 align:middle line:84%
So now we get to
the older Kozyrev,

00:28:24.920 --> 00:28:28.270 align:middle line:84%
and he's wondering why,
with all his publications,

00:28:28.270 --> 00:28:30.270 align:middle line:84%
no one is beating
a path to his door.

00:28:30.270 --> 00:28:33.530 align:middle line:84%
Like in the United States, if
you build a better mousetrap,

00:28:33.530 --> 00:28:34.880 align:middle line:90%
what will they do?

00:28:34.880 --> 00:28:36.130 align:middle line:90%
They won't even pay attention.

00:28:36.130 --> 00:28:38.210 align:middle line:90%
They'll go buy a cat.

00:28:38.210 --> 00:28:40.380 align:middle line:84%
Nobody said to
Kozyrev, oh, my god,

00:28:40.380 --> 00:28:42.590 align:middle line:84%
you've cracked the biggest
unified field theory

00:28:42.590 --> 00:28:43.870 align:middle line:90%
problem of all time.

00:28:43.870 --> 00:28:45.580 align:middle line:90%
They just basically ignored him.

00:28:45.580 --> 00:28:47.500 align:middle line:84%
And now what the KGB
has done-- or whatever

00:28:47.500 --> 00:28:49.930 align:middle line:84%
its current iteration
is-- they've attacked him

00:28:49.930 --> 00:28:51.880 align:middle line:84%
and his followers,
the scientists

00:28:51.880 --> 00:28:55.190 align:middle line:84%
trying to replicate his
experiments, as being anti this

00:28:55.190 --> 00:28:58.600 align:middle line:84%
and anti that and anti science
and in it for the money.

00:28:58.600 --> 00:29:00.030 align:middle line:84%
Does this sound
vaguely familiar?

00:29:00.030 --> 00:29:02.030 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: Sounds like what
goes on in this country.

00:29:02.030 --> 00:29:04.230 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: Kozyrev was
another incredible pioneer.

00:29:04.230 --> 00:29:06.070 align:middle line:84%
And the only thing
that makes me sad

00:29:06.070 --> 00:29:08.790 align:middle line:84%
is he didn't live
long enough to see us

00:29:08.790 --> 00:29:11.570 align:middle line:84%
independent guys in
the West replicating

00:29:11.570 --> 00:29:16.480 align:middle line:84%
his most fundamental experiments
and proving he was right.

00:29:16.480 --> 00:29:19.210 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: Well, it
reminds me of some

00:29:19.210 --> 00:29:22.990 align:middle line:84%
of the stories
from ancient India.

00:29:22.990 --> 00:29:26.770 align:middle line:84%
They seem to have maybe had
a handle on some of this.

00:29:26.770 --> 00:29:30.770 align:middle line:84%
And it makes me wonder
about the Mayans, also.

00:29:30.770 --> 00:29:33.130 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: Well, remember,
the Mayans are Indians.

00:29:33.130 --> 00:29:33.930 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: They are.

00:29:33.930 --> 00:29:35.241 align:middle line:90%
>>HOAGLAND: That's the long--

00:29:35.241 --> 00:29:35.990 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: It's right.

00:29:35.990 --> 00:29:38.024 align:middle line:84%
In fact, "Maya" means
"illusion" in Sanskrit.

00:29:38.024 --> 00:29:38.690 align:middle line:90%
>>HOAGLAND: Yes.

00:29:38.690 --> 00:29:40.800 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY: So when you
were in Central America

00:29:40.800 --> 00:29:43.855 align:middle line:84%
to measure the new physics at
several of the sacred Mayan

00:29:43.855 --> 00:29:45.870 align:middle line:84%
sites, at Teotihuacan,
especially,

00:29:45.870 --> 00:29:47.219 align:middle line:90%
what did you discover?

00:29:47.219 --> 00:29:48.510 align:middle line:90%
>>HOAGLAND: That they're right.

