00:30:42.770 --> 00:30:45.990 align:middle line:84%
Doing field work is
not all a bed of roses.

00:30:45.990 --> 00:30:48.970 align:middle line:84%
But we got astonishing
data, again,

00:30:48.970 --> 00:30:51.870 align:middle line:84%
all because of the
effect of these pyramids

00:30:51.870 --> 00:30:54.070 align:middle line:90%
on the little tuning fork.

00:30:54.070 --> 00:30:58.980 align:middle line:84%
The model was, in my mind,
if this physics was real,

00:30:58.980 --> 00:31:02.905 align:middle line:84%
the pyramids had to be so big
and so massive for one function

00:31:02.905 --> 00:31:08.800 align:middle line:84%
and one function only-- huge,
static, solid-state amplifiers

00:31:08.800 --> 00:31:10.140 align:middle line:90%
of the torsion field.

00:31:10.140 --> 00:31:11.130 align:middle line:90%
Because it's so tiny.

00:31:11.130 --> 00:31:13.910 align:middle line:84%
It's, like, 10 to the minus
fifth of other forces.

00:31:13.910 --> 00:31:17.810 align:middle line:84%
That's why Kozyrev said it's so
small that it's been bypassed

00:31:17.810 --> 00:31:21.280 align:middle line:84%
by most physicists, because they
don't deal in rotating systems.

00:31:21.280 --> 00:31:22.390 align:middle line:90%
They deal in non-rotating.

00:31:22.390 --> 00:31:24.330 align:middle line:84%
It's just simpler
in the machine shop

00:31:24.330 --> 00:31:26.650 align:middle line:84%
to make an experiment
that doesn't rotate.

00:31:26.650 --> 00:31:30.300 align:middle line:84%
So one of the predictions,
based on some Egyptian lore

00:31:30.300 --> 00:31:31.870 align:middle line:84%
that we don't have
time to go into,

00:31:31.870 --> 00:31:34.500 align:middle line:84%
was that, at dawn, if we stood
on the top of that pyramid,

00:31:34.500 --> 00:31:36.820 align:middle line:84%
that huge pyramid,
which in volume is about

00:31:36.820 --> 00:31:39.340 align:middle line:84%
equivalent to the
Great Pyramid at Giza,

00:31:39.340 --> 00:31:42.320 align:middle line:84%
there should be, at
sunrise, a dramatic change

00:31:42.320 --> 00:31:44.260 align:middle line:84%
in the torsion field,
which would change

00:31:44.260 --> 00:31:47.350 align:middle line:84%
the inertia of the tuning
fork, which would show up

00:31:47.350 --> 00:31:48.990 align:middle line:90%
as a change in the graph.

00:31:48.990 --> 00:31:51.100 align:middle line:84%
Now, on these graphs,
down is up and up is down.

00:31:51.100 --> 00:31:53.350 align:middle line:84%
For some reason, the guys
that wrote this program,

00:31:53.350 --> 00:31:56.280 align:middle line:84%
the increasing
frequency is down.

00:31:56.280 --> 00:31:57.780 align:middle line:84%
So when you see a
spike going down,

00:31:57.780 --> 00:32:00.510 align:middle line:84%
that's really going
up in frequency.

00:32:00.510 --> 00:32:03.880 align:middle line:84%
The only way the tuning
fork can change frequency

00:32:03.880 --> 00:32:07.390 align:middle line:84%
is if it either lost its
mind-- that's a metaphor--

00:32:07.390 --> 00:32:09.770 align:middle line:90%
or it lost mass.

00:32:09.770 --> 00:32:12.230 align:middle line:84%
And then it would
vibrate faster.

00:32:12.230 --> 00:32:15.700 align:middle line:84%
It vibrated faster
just at sunrise.

00:32:15.700 --> 00:32:16.460 align:middle line:90%
Look at the spike.

00:32:16.460 --> 00:32:17.920 align:middle line:90%
Look at the numbers.

00:32:17.920 --> 00:32:19.590 align:middle line:90%
It's 400 and some Hertz.

00:32:19.590 --> 00:32:22.550 align:middle line:84%
It normally vibrates
at 360 Hertz.

00:32:22.550 --> 00:32:24.890 align:middle line:90%
That's an impossible change.

00:32:24.890 --> 00:32:28.810 align:middle line:84%
And then, a few minutes later,
it did it again even more,

00:32:28.810 --> 00:32:34.030 align:middle line:84%
like a double hump,
double peak, at dawn.

00:32:34.030 --> 00:32:35.840 align:middle line:84%
This is why, by the
way, all prisoners

00:32:35.840 --> 00:32:38.240 align:middle line:90%
are shot at dawn, hung at dawn.

00:32:38.240 --> 00:32:42.230 align:middle line:84%
It's an ancient cultural
thingy that the physics at dawn

00:32:42.230 --> 00:32:44.890 align:middle line:84%
is different than at
other times of day.

00:32:44.890 --> 00:32:48.710 align:middle line:84%
This proves the
physics at dawn, which

00:32:48.710 --> 00:32:50.170 align:middle line:90%
gets back to the Egyptian.

00:32:50.170 --> 00:32:52.750 align:middle line:84%
So what was the name
of the big guy in Egypt

00:32:52.750 --> 00:32:55.199 align:middle line:90%
who was the god of sunrise?

00:32:55.199 --> 00:32:55.740 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Horace

00:32:55.740 --> 00:32:56.531 align:middle line:90%
>>HOAGLAND: Horace.

00:32:56.531 --> 00:32:57.350 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Horizon.

00:32:57.350 --> 00:32:59.246 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: Horace
of the horizon.

00:32:59.246 --> 00:33:01.310 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: Right.

00:33:01.310 --> 00:33:06.365 align:middle line:84%
So because the sun
is at 90 degrees,

00:33:06.365 --> 00:33:07.977 align:middle line:90%
it has an impact just like--

00:33:07.977 --> 00:33:10.060 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: Well, think
of it as you're on a ball,

00:33:10.060 --> 00:33:11.710 align:middle line:84%
and you're rotating
toward the sun.

00:33:11.710 --> 00:33:15.040 align:middle line:84%
The maximum rotation-- it's
more interesting than that,

00:33:15.040 --> 00:33:18.390 align:middle line:84%
but the maximum rotation is
at dawn, at the terminator.

00:33:18.390 --> 00:33:20.710 align:middle line:84%
It's actually more
like the angles.

00:33:20.710 --> 00:33:22.880 align:middle line:84%
90 degrees is important
in the physics.

00:33:22.880 --> 00:33:24.260 align:middle line:90%
180 is important.

00:33:24.260 --> 00:33:26.130 align:middle line:84%
That's why conjunctions,
things lined up,

00:33:26.130 --> 00:33:29.400 align:middle line:84%
or anticonjunctions, things on
the opposite side of the sun,

00:33:29.400 --> 00:33:30.330 align:middle line:90%
are important.

00:33:30.330 --> 00:33:32.180 align:middle line:84%
It's all ultimately
about the angles.

00:33:32.180 --> 00:33:35.160 align:middle line:84%
Remember when Clinton was
running for president,

00:33:35.160 --> 00:33:37.390 align:middle line:90%
and it was the economy, stupid?

00:33:37.390 --> 00:33:38.000 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:33:38.000 --> 00:33:38.850 align:middle line:90%
>>JAY: It's the angles, stupid.

00:33:38.850 --> 00:33:40.433 align:middle line:84%
>>HOAGLAND: It's the
